channel.title: SkyLearn Pre-Filter Test Feed – New Batch v3
channel.description: Ten new articles for advanced keyword and context validation

item.title: CBRE relocates European headquarters to refurbished offices at Paddington Square
item.description: CBRE has moved its London HQ into a 220,000 sq ft space at Paddington Square, marking a major consolidation of its UK offices.

item.title: Coldplay announce stadium tour across Europe for summer 2026
item.description: The band will perform 15 shows across major European cities next year as part of their sustainability-themed tour.

item.title: Legal & General to develop new mixed-use office scheme in Manchester’s St John’s district
item.description: The insurer has signed contractors to deliver a 180,000 sq ft workspace targeting creative and tech occupiers.

item.title: BBC launches new streaming service for international audiences
item.description: The platform will offer live and on-demand access to UK-produced TV content worldwide.

item.title: PwC expands Belfast operations with new 200,000 sq ft waterfront office
item.description: The professional services firm has signed a long-term lease for Merchant Square 2, aiming to support 3,000 employees in Northern Ireland.

item.title: Netflix reveals first trailer for upcoming sci-fi blockbuster
item.description: The streaming giant has released the teaser for its highly anticipated 2026 summer release, “Eclipse Protocol”.

item.title: KPMG signs lease for new regional office at Birmingham Paradise development
item.description: KPMG has agreed terms on a 90,000 sq ft office at One Centenary Way, with staff expected to move in early 2026.

item.title: David Beckham opens youth sports foundation in East London
item.description: The former footballer launched a new community initiative supporting grassroots football across the capital.

item.title: Capita completes consolidation of UK offices into new London Bridge HQ
item.description: Capita has relocated teams from five sites into a single 250,000 sq ft headquarters designed for hybrid working and energy efficiency.

item.title: Emma Raducanu returns to competition with Australian Open warm-up victory
item.description: The British tennis star defeated her first-round opponent in straight sets after an 11-month break from professional play.
